  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nIn StateArchiver logic to prune states, epoch is used a key to index and prune states, which are actually indexed by slot\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/db9450ba2ee4ac90469999450a16d143f6127961/packages/beacon-node/src/chain/archiver/archiveStates.ts#L48-L52\r\n\r\nCurrent parameters in to persists \"recent\" states every 32 epochs, older states every 1024 epochs\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/db9450ba2ee4ac90469999450a16d143f6127961/packages/beacon-node/src/chain/archiver/archiveStates.ts#L30-L39\r\n\r\nHowever, now Lodestar is persisting states every 32 epochs always. Since states are reasonably heavy for Mainnet and Prater (~40MB) that means (82187 epochs in 1 year)\r\n\r\n| Store state every N epochs | State DB growth per year |\r\n| - | - |\r\n| every 32 | 102 GB |\r\n| every 1024 | 3.2 GB |\r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nApply designed parameters, index by slot",
